metrics_conclusion: Trust Love (feat Casey Lee Williams) has higher complexity than the average song  in terms Chord Complexity, Chord Progression Novelty and Chord-Bass Melody.
key_conclusion:
Trust Love (feat Casey Lee Williams) is written in the key of A Minor.  

According to the Theorytab database, it is the most popular key among Minor keys and     the 7th most popular  among all keys. Minor keys, along with major keys, are a common choice for popular music.  The three most important chords, built off the 1st, 4th and 5th scale degrees are all minor chords (A minor, D minor, and E minor).

metadata.editComments:
Was too lazy to do the melody, but maybe I'll come back and add it later, if no one beats me too it.

Some of the functionalities are a little wacked, but all the chords should be right. For example, vii7 from Phrygian is really functioning like a secondary predominant rather than a borrowed chord, ii7/VI. Also, a lot of the more colorful "borrowed" chords function more like quick modulations to other key centers, rather than chords borrowed from a parallel mode to A minor.
